text.0: @kelechukuiruoma @thefactcheckhub We're working to verify this claim. We will publish it as soon as it is done. Thank you.
text.1: The viral claim that the United Nations has to intervene after 30 days of protest is False. According to 2(7) of its charter, the UN does not have the right to interfere in the domestic affairs of any member country. Read the facts: https://t.co/JxsJ8UEsUs #DubawaChecks #EndSARS
text.2: Some accounts on Twitter shared a picture of at least 9 dead bodies lined side by side, suggesting that they were killed during the ongoing #EndSARS protests but findings show that they were victims of bandit attacks in Kaduna. Read more here:https://t.co/2R3NEx8KMj #DubawaChecks
text.3: A report by  Authority Newspaper that Zahra Buhari and Kiki Osinbajo brought about the dissolution of SARS is misleading. They did not influence the #EndSARS movement in any special way. They also didn’t join or lead any protest. Read here: https://t.co/5rB5LgU17C #DubawaChecks
